RELEVANT NOTES (SECTION + CHAPTER):
=== SECTION 17 NOTES ===
SECTION XVII - VEHICLES, AIRCRAFT, VESSELS AND ASSOCIATED TRANSPORT EQUIPMENT

Notes:
1. This section does NOT cover articles of heading 9503 or 9508, or sleds, bobsleds, toboggans, or the like (heading 9506).

2. "Parts" and "parts and accessories" do NOT apply to:
   (a) Joints, washers, or the like of any material (classified by constituent material or in heading 8484) or other articles of vulcanized rubber other than hard rubber (heading 4016);
   (b) Parts of general use (section XV note 2) of base metal, or similar goods of plastics (chapter 39);
   (c) Articles of chapter 82 (tools);
   (d) Articles of heading 8306;
   (e) Machines or apparatus of headings 8401-8479, or parts thereof, other than radiators for section XVII articles; articles of heading 8481 or 8482, or (provided they constitute integral parts of engines or motors) articles of heading 8483;
   (f) Electrical machinery or equipment (chapter 85);
   (g) Articles of chapter 90;
   (h) Articles of chapter 91;
   (ij) Arms (chapter 93);
   (k) Luminaires and lighting fittings and parts (heading 9405);
   (l) Brushes for vehicle parts (heading 9603).

3. References in chapters 86-88 to "parts" or "accessories" do NOT apply to parts or accessories not suitable for use solely or principally with those chapters' articles. Part or accessory matching two or more chapter headings → classify under heading corresponding to principal use.

4. For this section:
   (a) Vehicles for both road and rail → appropriate chapter 87 heading;
   (b) Amphibious motor vehicles → appropriate chapter 87 heading;
   (c) Aircraft that can also be used as road vehicles → appropriate chapter 88 heading.

5. AIR-CUSHION VEHICLES classification:
   (a) Designed for guide-track travel (hovertrains) → chapter 86;
   (b) Designed for land or both land and water → chapter 87;
   (c) Designed for water (whether or not able to land on beaches or landing-stages, or travel over ice) → chapter 89.

   Parts and accessories of air-cushion vehicles → classify same way as vehicles they are classified with.
   Hovertrain track fixtures and fittings → railway track fixtures and fittings. Signaling, safety, or traffic control equipment for hovertrain systems → equipment for railways.

=== CHAPTER 87 NOTES ===
CHAPTER 87 - VEHICLES OTHER THAN RAILWAY OR TRAMWAY ROLLING STOCK, AND PARTS AND ACCESSORIES THEREOF

Notes:
1. This chapter does NOT cover railway or tramway rolling stock designed solely for running on rails.

2. "Tractors" = vehicles constructed essentially for hauling or pushing another vehicle, appliance, or load, whether or not they contain subsidiary provision for transport (in connection with main tractor use) of tools, seeds, fertilizers, or other goods.

3. Machines and working tools designed for fitting to tractors (heading 8701) as interchangeable equipment remain classified in their respective headings even if presented with tractor, and whether or not mounted on it.

4. Motor chassis fitted with cabs → headings 8702-8704, NOT heading 8706.

5. Heading 8712 includes all children's bicycles. Other children's cycles → heading 9503.

Subheading Note:
Subheading 8708.22.00 covers:
(a) Front windscreens (windshields), rear windows, other windows, framed;
(b) Front windscreens, rear windows, other windows (whether or not framed) incorporating heating devices or other electrical or electronic devices;
when suitable for use solely or principally with motor vehicles of headings 8701-8705.

Additional U.S. Notes:
1. Road tractors, trailers, and semi-trailers remain separately classified in headings 8701 and 8716, even when entered together.

2. Bicycle wheel diameter (heading 8712) = diameter measured to outer circumference of tire mounted thereon, or if none mounted, of usual tire for such wheel.

Statistical Note:
"New" motor vehicles (headings 8701, 8703) = produced or assembled but not sold to any person or entity other than manufacturer, distributor, or dealer.
"Used" motor vehicles = vehicles whose equitable or legal title has been transferred via first sale by manufacturer, distributor, or dealer to ultimate purchaser.

=== SECTION 16 NOTES ===
SECTION XVI - MACHINERY AND MECHANICAL APPLIANCES; ELECTRICAL EQUIPMENT; PARTS THEREOF; SOUND RECORDERS AND REPRODUCERS, TELEVISION IMAGE AND SOUND RECORDERS AND REPRODUCERS, AND PARTS AND ACCESSORIES OF SUCH ARTICLES

Notes:
1. This section does NOT cover:
   (a) Transmission, conveyor, or elevator belts of plastics (chapter 39) or vulcanized rubber (heading 4010); other articles of vulcanized rubber other than hard rubber for technical uses (heading 4016);
   (b) Articles of leather or composition leather (heading 4205) or furskin (heading 4303) for technical uses;
   (c) Bobbins, spools, cops, cones, cores, reels, or similar supports of any material;
   (d) Perforated cards for Jacquard or similar machines;
   (e) Textile transmission or conveyor belts (heading 5910) or other textile articles for technical uses (heading 5911);
   (f) Precious or semiprecious stones (headings 7102-7104), or articles wholly of such stones (heading 7116), EXCEPT unmounted worked sapphires and diamonds for styli (heading 8522);
   (g) Parts of general use (section XV note 2) of base metal, or similar goods of plastics (chapter 39);
   (h) Drill pipe (heading 7304);
   (ij) Endless belts of metal wire or strip (section XV);
   (k) Articles of chapter 82 or 83;
   (l) Articles of section XVII;
   (m) Articles of chapter 90;
   (n) Clocks, watches, or other chapter 91 articles;
   (o) Interchangeable tools (heading 8207) or brushes as machine parts (heading 9603); similar interchangeable tools classified by working part constituent material;
   (p) Articles of chapter 95;
   (q) Typewriter or similar ribbons (classified by constituent material, or heading 9612 if inked), or monopods, bipods, tripods and similar (heading 9620).

2. PARTS OF MACHINES (not being parts of headings 8484, 8544, 8545, 8546, 8547) classification:
   (a) Parts which are goods of any chapter 84 or 85 heading (other than 8409, 8431, 8448, 8466, 8473, 8487, 8503, 8522, 8529, 8538, 8548) → classify in their respective headings;
   (b) Other parts for use solely or principally with particular kind of machine, or machines of same heading (including 8479 or 8543) → classify with those machines or in heading 8409, 8431, 8448, 8466, 8473, 8503, 8522, 8529, or 8538. Parts equally suitable for headings 8517 and 8525-8528 → heading 8517. Parts solely or principally for heading 8524 → heading 8529;
   (c) All other parts → heading 8409, 8431, 8448, 8466, 8473, 8503, 8522, 8529, or 8538, or failing that, heading 8487 or 8548.

3. COMPOSITE MACHINES: machines consisting of two or more machines fitted together forming a whole, or designed for two or more complementary or alternative functions → classify as if consisting only of component or machine performing principal function.

4. FUNCTIONAL UNITS: where machine consists of individual components (separate or interconnected by piping, transmission devices, electric cables, or other devices) intended to contribute together to clearly defined function covered by chapter 84 or 85 heading → whole classified in heading appropriate to that function.

5. "Machine" = any machine, machinery, plant, equipment, apparatus, or appliance cited in chapter 84 or 85 headings.

6. ELECTRICAL AND ELECTRONIC WASTE AND SCRAP:
   (A) = electrical and electronic assemblies, printed circuit boards, and electrical or electronic articles that:
       (a) are rendered unusable for original purposes by breakage, cutting-up, wear, or other processes, or are economically unsuitable for repair, refurbishment, or renovation; AND
       (b) are packaged or shipped in manner not intended to protect individual articles from damage during transportation, loading, and unloading.
   (B) Mixed consignments of "electrical and electronic waste and scrap" and other waste and scrap → heading 8549.
   (C) Does NOT cover municipal waste (chapter 38 note 4).

Additional U.S. Note:
"Printed circuit assembly" = goods consisting of one or more printed circuits (heading 8534) with one or more active elements assembled thereon, with or without passive elements. "Active elements" = diodes, transistors, similar semiconductor devices (whether or not photosensitive) of heading 8541, and integrated circuits of heading 8542.

=== CHAPTER 84 NOTES ===
CHAPTER 84 - NUCLEAR REACTORS, BOILERS, MACHINERY AND MECHANICAL APPLIANCES; PARTS THEREOF

Notes:
1. This chapter does NOT cover:
   (a) Millstones, grindstones, or other articles of chapter 68;
   (b) Machinery or appliances (e.g., pumps) of ceramic material and ceramic parts of machinery or appliances of any material (chapter 69);
   (c) Laboratory glassware (heading 7017); machinery, appliances, or other articles for technical uses or parts thereof, of glass (heading 7019 or 7020);
   (d) Articles of heading 7321 or 7322 or similar articles of other base metals (chapters 74-76 or 78-81);
   (e) Vacuum cleaners (heading 8508);
   (f) Electromechanical domestic appliances (heading 8509); digital cameras (heading 8525);
   (g) Radiators for section XVII articles;
   (h) Hand-operated mechanical floor sweepers, not motorized (heading 9603).

2. Subject to section XVI note 3 and chapter 84 note 11: machine or appliance matching description in headings 8401-8424 OR heading 8486, AND also matching headings 8425-8480 → classify under the former group or heading 8486, NOT the latter group.

   (A) Heading 8419 does NOT cover:
       (i) Germination plant, incubators, or brooders (heading 8436);
       (ii) Grain dampening machines (heading 8437);
       (iii) Diffusing apparatus for sugar juice extraction (heading 8438);
       (iv) Machinery for heat-treatment of textile yarns, fabrics, or made up textile articles (heading 8451);
       (v) Machinery, plant, or laboratory equipment designed for mechanical operation where temperature change (even if necessary) is subsidiary.

   (B) Heading 8422 does NOT cover:
       (i) Sewing machines for closing bags or similar containers (heading 8452);
       (ii) Office machinery (heading 8472).

   (C) Heading 8424 does NOT cover:
       (i) Ink-jet printing machines (heading 8443);
       (ii) Water-jet cutting machines (heading 8456).

3. Machine tool for working any material matching description in heading 8456 AND heading 8457, 8458, 8459, 8460, 8461, 8464, or 8465 → classify in heading 8456.

4. Heading 8457 applies ONLY to machine tools for working metal (other than lathes including turning centers) that can carry out different types of machining operations either:
   (a) By automatic tool change from magazine or the like in conformity with machining program (machining centers);
   (b) By automatic use, simultaneously or sequentially, of different unit heads working on fixed position workpiece (unit construction machines, single station);
   (c) By automatic transfer of workpiece to different unit heads (multi-station transfer machines).

5. For heading 8462:
   - "Slitting line" for flat products = processing line composed of uncoiler, coil flattener, slitter, and recoiler.
   - "Cut-to-length line" for flat products = processing line composed of uncoiler, coil flattener, and shear.

6. AUTOMATIC DATA PROCESSING MACHINES (heading 8471):
   (A) "Automatic data processing machines" = machines capable of:
       (i) Storing processing program(s) and at least the data immediately necessary for execution;
       (ii) Being freely programmed per user requirements;
       (iii) Performing arithmetical computations specified by user;
       (iv) Executing, without human intervention, a processing program requiring them to modify execution by logical decision during processing run.

   (B) ADP machines may be systems consisting of variable number of separate units.

   (C) A unit is part of an ADP system IF it meets ALL of:
       (i) Is of a kind solely or principally used in ADP system;
       (ii) Is connectable to CPU either directly or through one or more other units;
       (iii) Is able to accept or deliver data in form (codes or signals) usable by the system.

       Separately presented units of ADP machine → heading 8471.
       HOWEVER: keyboards, X-Y coordinate input devices, and disk storage units satisfying (C)(ii) and (C)(iii) → in all cases classified as units of heading 8471.

   (D) Heading 8471 does NOT cover the following when presented separately (even if meeting all conditions of note 6(C)):
       (i) Printers, copying machines, facsimile machines, whether or not combined;
       (ii) Apparatus for transmission or reception of voice, images, or other data, including apparatus for communication in wired or wireless network (LAN or WAN);
       (iii) Loudspeakers and microphones;
       (iv) Television cameras, digital cameras, and video camera recorders;
       (v) Monitors and projectors not incorporating television reception apparatus.

   (E) Machines incorporating or working in conjunction with ADP machine and performing specific function other than data processing → classify in headings appropriate to their respective functions or, failing that, in residual headings.

7. Heading 8482: applies inter alia to polished steel balls with max and min diameters not differing from nominal diameter by more than 1% or 0.05 mm, whichever is less. Other steel balls → heading 7326.

8. Machine used for more than one purpose → classified by principal purpose as if sole purpose.

   Subject to chapter 84 note 2 and section XVI note 3: machine whose principal purpose is not described in any heading, OR for which no one purpose is principal → heading 8479 (unless context requires otherwise).

   Heading 8479 also covers machines for making rope or cable (stranding, twisting, or cabling machines) from metal wire, textile yarn, or any other material or combination.

9. "Pocket-size" (heading 8470) = machines with dimensions not exceeding 170 mm × 100 mm × 45 mm.

10. "Additive manufacturing" (also "3D printing") (heading 8485) = formation of physical objects, based on digital model, by successive addition and layering, and consolidation and solidification of material (e.g., metal, plastics, ceramics).

    Subject to section XVI note 1 and chapter 84 note 1: machines matching heading 8485 description → classify in that heading and no other tariff schedule heading.

11. SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICES AND ELECTRONIC INTEGRATED CIRCUITS (heading 8486):
    (A) Chapter 85 notes 12(a) and 12(b) also apply to "semiconductor devices" and "electronic integrated circuits" as used in this note and heading 8486. HOWEVER: for this note and heading 8486, "semiconductor devices" ALSO covers photosensitive semiconductor devices and light emitting diodes (LED).

    (B) "Manufacture of flat panel displays" = fabrication of substrates into flat panel. Does NOT cover manufacture of glass or assembly of printed circuit boards or other electronic components onto flat panel. "Flat panel display" does NOT cover cathode-ray tube technology.

    (C) Heading 8486 ALSO includes machines and apparatus solely or principally for:
        (i) Manufacture or repair of masks and reticles;
        (ii) Assembling semiconductor devices or electronic integrated circuits;
        (iii) Lifting, handling, loading, or unloading of boules, wafers, semiconductor devices, electronic integrated circuits, and flat panel displays.

    (D) Subject to section XVI note 1 and chapter 84 note 1: machines and apparatus matching heading 8486 description → classify in that heading and no other tariff schedule heading.

Subheading Notes:
1. "Machining centers" (subheading 8465.20) = ONLY machine tools for working wood, cork, bone, hard rubber, hard plastics, or similar hard materials, which can carry out different types of machining operations by automatic tool change from magazine or the like in conformity with machining program.

2. "Systems" (subheading 8471.49) = ADP machines whose units satisfy chapter 84 note 6(C) conditions and which comprise at least a CPU, one input unit (e.g., keyboard or scanner), and one output unit (e.g., visual display unit or printer).

3. "Valves for oleohydraulic or pneumatic transmissions" (subheading 8481.20) = valves used specifically in transmission of "fluid power" in hydraulic or pneumatic system where energy source is pressurized fluids (liquid or gas). May be any type (pressure-reducing, check, etc.). Subheading 8481.20 takes PRECEDENCE over all other subheadings of heading 8481.

4. Subheading 8482.40 applies ONLY to bearings with cylindrical rollers of uniform diameter ≤5 mm and length ≥3× diameter. Ends of rollers may be rounded.

Additional U.S. Notes:
1. For subheadings 8479.89.65 and 8479.89.95: "Free (C)" rate applies ONLY to: nonelectric starter motors; propeller regulators (nonelectric); servo-mechanisms (nonelectric); windshield wipers (nonelectric); hydropneumatic accumulators; pneumatic starters for turbojets, turbopropellers, or other gas turbines; toilet units specially designed for aircraft; mechanical actuators for thrust reversers.

2. Subheading 8443.99.20 covers parts of printer units (subheading 8443.32.10):
   (a) Control or command assemblies (incorporating >1 of: printed circuit assembly, hard or flexible disk drive, keyboard, user interface);
   (b) Light source assemblies (incorporating >1 of: LED assembly, gas laser, mirror polygon assembly, base casting);
   (c) Laser imaging assemblies (incorporating >1 of: photoreceptor belt or cylinder, toner receptacle unit, toner developing unit, charge/discharge units, cleaning unit);
   (d) Image fixing assemblies (incorporating >1 of: fuser, pressure roller, heating element, release oil dispenser, cleaning unit, electrical control);
   (e) Ink jet marking assemblies (incorporating >1 of: thermal print head, ink dispensing unit, nozzle and reservoir unit, ink heater);
   (f) Maintenance/sealing assemblies (incorporating >1 of: vacuum unit, ink jet covering unit, sealing unit, purging unit);
   (g) Paper handling assemblies (incorporating >1 of: paper transport belt, roller, print bar, carriage, gripper roller, paper storage unit, exit tray);
   (h) Thermal transfer imaging assemblies (incorporating >1 of: thermal print head, cleaning unit, supply or take-up roller);
   (ij) Ionographic imaging assemblies (incorporating >1 of: ion generation and emitting unit, air assist unit, printed circuit assembly, charge receptor belt or cylinder, toner receptacle unit, toner distribution unit, developer receptacle and distribution unit, developing unit, charge/discharge unit, cleaning unit);
   (k) Combinations of above specified assemblies.

3. Subheading 8443.99.30 covers parts of facsimile machines:
   (a) Control or command assemblies (incorporating >1 of: printed circuit assembly, modem, hard or flexible disk drive, keyboard, user interface);
   (b) Optics module assemblies (incorporating >1 of: optics lamp, charge couples device and appropriate optics, lenses, mirrors);
   (c) Laser imaging assemblies (incorporating >1 of: photoreceptor belt or cylinder, toner receptacle unit, toner developing unit, charge/discharge units, cleaning unit);
   (d) Ink jet marking assemblies (incorporating >1 of: thermal print head, ink dispensing unit, nozzle and reservoir unit, ink heater);
   (e) Thermal transfer imaging assemblies (incorporating >1 of: thermal print head, cleaning unit, supply or take-up roller);
   (f) Ionographic imaging assemblies (incorporating >1 of: ion generation and emitting unit, air assist unit, printed circuit assembly, charge receptor belt or cylinder, toner receptacle unit, toner distribution unit, developer receptacle and distribution unit, developing unit, charge/discharge unit, cleaning unit);
   (g) Image fixing assemblies (incorporating >1 of: fuser, pressure roller, heating elements, release oil dispenser, cleaning unit, electrical control);
   (h) Paper handling assemblies (incorporating >1 of: paper transport belt, roller, print bar, carriage, gripper roller, paper storage unit, exit tray);
   (ij) Combinations of above specified assemblies.

4. Subheading 8443.99.40 covers parts of photocopying apparatus (subheading 8443.39.20):
   (a) Imaging assemblies (incorporating >1 of: photoreceptor belt or cylinder, toner receptacle unit, toner distribution unit, developer receptacle unit, developer distribution unit, charge/discharge unit, cleaning unit);
   (b) Optics assemblies (incorporating >1 of: lens, mirror, illumination source, document exposure glass);
   (c) User control assemblies (incorporating >1 of: printed circuit assembly, power supply, user input keyboard, wiring harness, display unit (CRT or flat panel));
   (d) Image fixing assemblies (incorporating >1 of: fuser, pressure rollers, heating elements, release oil dispenser, cleaning unit, electrical controls);
   (e) Paper handling assemblies (incorporating >1 of: paper transport belt, roller, print bar, carriage, gripper roller, paper storage unit, exit tray);
   (f) Combinations of above specified assemblies.

Statistical Notes:
1. "Industrial turbines" (8411.81.8010, 8411.82.8010) = ONLY gas turbines used in stationary applications, including for stationary power generation.
2. Wind turbine blades shall be counted individually, NOT as blade sets.
3. "Sucker rods" (8413.91.9065) includes pony rods and polished rods, all designed for oil well and oil field related pumps.
4. "Aerial work platforms" (8427.10.8020, 8427.10.8040, 8427.10.8070, 8427.20.8020, 8427.90.0020) = works trucks incorporating platform attached to lift mechanism mounted on mobile base, for lifting personnel, tools, and materials.
5. "Note counters and note scanners" (8472.90.9040) = document handling machines that count currency bills, bank notes, coupons, script, or other value-based paper documents and stack them in organized fashion. Both may incorporate sensor for detecting counterfeit documents. Note scanners have additional sensors to distinguish documents by denomination.
6. "Gear boxes and speed changers for wind turbines" (8483.40.5020) = all configurations of gear boxes and speed changers designed for wind turbines, including fixed ratio, multiple ratio, and variable ratio speed changers.

=== CHAPTER 85 NOTES ===
CHAPTER 85 - ELECTRICAL MACHINERY AND EQUIPMENT AND PARTS THEREOF; SOUND RECORDERS AND REPRODUCERS, TELEVISION IMAGE AND SOUND RECORDERS AND REPRODUCERS, AND PARTS AND ACCESSORIES OF SUCH ARTICLES

Notes:
1. This chapter does NOT cover:
   (a) Electrically warmed blankets, bed pads, foot-muffs, clothing, footwear, ear pads, or other articles worn on person;
   (b) Articles of glass (heading 7011);
   (c) Machines and apparatus (heading 8486);
   (d) Vacuum apparatus for medical, surgical, dental, or veterinary sciences (heading 9018);
   (e) Electrically heated furniture (chapter 94).

2. Headings 8501-8504 do NOT apply to goods of heading 8511, 8512, 8540, 8541, or 8542. HOWEVER: metal tank mercury arc rectifiers remain in heading 8504.

3. "Electric accumulators" (heading 8507) includes those with ancillary components for storing and supplying energy or protection (electrical connectors, temperature control devices, circuit protection devices). May include portion of protective housing.

4. Heading 8509 covers ONLY electromechanical machines commonly used for domestic purposes:
   (a) Floor polishers, food grinders and mixers, fruit or vegetable juice extractors, of any weight;
   (b) Other machines ≤20 kg (exclusive of extra interchangeable parts or detachable auxiliary devices).
   EXCLUDES: fans, ventilating or recycling hoods with fan (heading 8414), centrifugal clothes dryers (heading 8421), dishwashing machines (heading 8422), household washing machines (heading 8450), ironing machines (heading 8420 or 8451), sewing machines (heading 8452), electric scissors (heading 8467), electrothermic appliances (heading 8516).

5. "Smartphones" (heading 8517) = cellular network telephones with mobile operating system for ADP machine functions (downloading and running multiple applications simultaneously, including third-party applications), whether or not integrating digital cameras, navigational aid systems, etc.

6. For heading 8523:
   (a) "Solid-state non-volatile storage devices" (e.g., flash memory cards) = storage devices with connecting socket, comprising one or more flash memories (FLASH E²PROM) as integrated circuits on printed circuit board. May include controller IC and discrete passive components;
   (b) "Smart cards" = cards with embedded electronic integrated circuits (microprocessor, RAM, or ROM) as chips. May contain contacts, magnetic stripe, or embedded antenna, but NO other active or passive circuit elements.

7. "Flat panel display modules" (heading 8524) = devices for information display equipped with at least a display screen, designed for incorporation into articles of other headings before use. Display screens may be flat, curved, flexible, foldable, or stretchable. May incorporate elements for receiving video signals and allocating to pixels. Does NOT include modules with video signal conversion components (scaler IC, decoder IC, application processor) or modules that have assumed character of other heading goods.
   Heading 8524 takes PRECEDENCE over any other tariff heading.

8. "Printed circuits" (heading 8534) = circuits obtained by forming on insulating base (by printing, embossing, plating-up, etching, or film circuit technique) conductor elements, contacts, or other printed components (inductances, resistors, capacitors) alone or interconnected according to pre-established pattern. EXCLUDES elements that can produce, rectify, modulate, or amplify electrical signal (semiconductor elements). Does NOT cover circuits combined with elements other than those from printing process, nor individual discrete resistors, capacitors, or inductances. May be fitted with non-printed connecting elements.
   Thin- or thick-film circuits with passive and active elements from same process → heading 8542.

9. "Connectors for optical fibres, optical fibre bundles or cables" (heading 8536) = connectors that simply mechanically align optical fibres end to end in digital line system. No other function (no amplification, regeneration, or signal modification).

10. Heading 8537 does NOT include cordless infrared devices for remote control of television receivers or other electrical equipment (heading 8543).

11. "Light-emitting diode (LED) light sources" (heading 8539):
    (a) "LED modules" = electrical light sources based on LEDs in electrical circuits, containing further elements (electrical, mechanical, thermal, optical). Also contain discrete active or passive elements, or heading 8536 or 8542 articles for power supply or control. Do NOT have cap for easy installation or replacement in luminaire;
    (b) "LED lamps" = electrical light sources containing one or more LED modules plus further elements. HAVE cap for easy installation or replacement in luminaire and ensuring mechanical and electrical contact.

12. For headings 8541 and 8542:
    (a)(i) "Semiconductor devices" = devices whose operation depends on resistivity variations on electric field application, or semiconductor-based transducers.

    "Semiconductor-based transducers" = semiconductor-based sensors, actuators, resonators, and oscillators that perform intrinsic function and convert physical or chemical phenomena to electrical signal or vice versa. Elements are indivisibly combined.

    Definitions:
    - "Semiconductor-based" = built on semiconductor substrate, made of semiconductor materials, or manufactured by semiconductor technology where semiconductor plays critical role;
    - "Physical or chemical phenomena" = pressure, acoustic waves, acceleration, vibration, movement, orientation, strain, magnetic field strength, electric field strength, light, radioactivity, humidity, flow, chemical concentration;
    - "Semiconductor-based sensor" = detects physical or chemical quantities and converts to electric signals;
    - "Semiconductor-based actuator" = converts electric signals into physical movement;
    - "Semiconductor-based resonator" = generates mechanical or electrical oscillation of predefined frequency in response to external input;
    - "Semiconductor-based oscillator" = generates mechanical or electrical oscillation of predefined frequency.

    (a)(ii) "Light-emitting diodes (LED)" = semiconductor devices converting electrical energy to visible, infra-red, or ultra-violet rays, whether or not electrically connected or combined with protective diodes. LEDs of heading 8541 do NOT incorporate elements for power supply or control;

    (b) "Electronic integrated circuits":
        (i) Monolithic integrated circuits = circuit elements (diodes, transistors, resistors, capacitors, inductances) created in mass and on surface of semiconductor or compound semiconductor material, inseparably associated;
        (ii) Hybrid integrated circuits = passive elements (thin- or thick-film technology) + active elements (semiconductor technology) combined indivisibly by interconnections on single insulating substrate (glass, ceramic). May include discrete components;
        (iii) Multichip integrated circuits = two or more interconnected monolithic ICs combined indivisibly, with or without insulating substrates, with or without leadframes, but no other active or passive circuit elements;
        (iv) Multi-component integrated circuits (MCOs) = combination of one or more monolithic, hybrid, or multichip ICs with at least one of: silicon-based sensors, actuators, oscillators, resonators, or combinations; or components performing heading 8532, 8533, 8541 functions, or inductors (heading 8504), formed indivisibly into single body for PCB assembly.

    Headings 8541 and 8542 take PRECEDENCE over any other tariff heading, EXCEPT heading 8523 which might cover them by function reference.

Subheading Notes:
1. Subheading 8525.81: high-speed television cameras, digital cameras, video camera recorders with: writing speed >0.5 mm/μs, time resolution ≤50 ns, or frame rate >225,000 fps.
2. Subheading 8525.82: radiation-hardened or radiation-tolerant cameras designed for high-radiation environment, withstanding total radiation dose ≥50×10³ Gy (5×10⁶ RAD silicon).
3. Subheading 8525.83: night vision cameras using photocathode to convert light to electrons for amplification and visible image. EXCLUDES thermal imaging cameras.
4. Subheading 8527.12: cassette players with built-in amplifier, without built-in loudspeaker, no external power needed, dimensions ≤170 mm × 100 mm × 45 mm.
5. Subheadings 8549.11-8549.19: "spent primary cells, spent primary batteries and spent electric accumulators" = those unusable because of breakage, cutting-up, wear, or other reasons, nor capable of being recharged.

Additional U.S. Notes:
1. For headings 8501 and 8503: 746 W = 1 hp.
2. "Toasters" (subheading 8516.72) includes toaster-ovens designed essentially for toasting bread but can also bake small items.
3. "Transceivers" (headings 8517 and 8525) = combinations of radio transmitting and receiving equipment in common housing, using common circuit components for both, NOT capable of simultaneously receiving and transmitting.

=== CHAPTER 86 NOTES ===
CHAPTER 86 - RAILWAY OR TRAMWAY LOCOMOTIVES, ROLLING STOCK AND PARTS THEREOF; RAILWAY OR TRAMWAY TRACK FIXTURES AND FITTINGS AND PARTS THEREOF; MECHANICAL (INCLUDING ELECTRO-MECHANICAL) TRAFFIC SIGNALING EQUIPMENT OF ALL KINDS

Notes:
1. This chapter does NOT cover:
   (a) Railway or tramway sleepers (cross-ties) of wood or concrete, or concrete guide-track sections for hovertrains (heading 4406 or 6810);
   (b) Railway or tramway track construction material of iron or steel (heading 7302);
   (c) Electrical signaling, safety, or traffic control equipment (heading 8530).

2. Heading 8607 applies inter alia to:
   (a) Axles, wheels, wheel sets (running gear), metal tires, hoops, hubs, and other wheel parts;
   (b) Frames, underframes, truck assemblies;
   (c) Axle boxes; brake gear;
   (d) Buffers for rolling-stock; hooks and other coupling gear and corridor connections;
   (e) Coachwork.

3. Subject to note 1, heading 8608 applies inter alia to:
   (a) Assembled track, turntables, platform buffers, loading gauges;
   (b) Semaphores, mechanical signal discs, level crossing control gear, signal and point controls, and other mechanical (including electro-mechanical) signaling, safety, or traffic control equipment (whether or not fitted for electric lighting) for railways, tramways, roads, inland waterways, parking facilities, port installations, or airfields.

Additional U.S. Note:
Railway locomotives (headings 8601, 8602) and railway freight cars (heading 8606) with no duty owed are NOT subject to entry or release requirements under Tariff Act sections 448 and 484. Secretary of the Treasury may establish reporting requirements, including bond requirements for compliance.

=== CHAPTER 84 NOTES ===
CHAPTER 84 - NUCLEAR REACTORS, BOILERS, MACHINERY AND MECHANICAL APPLIANCES; PARTS THEREOF

Notes:
1. This chapter does NOT cover:
   (a) Millstones, grindstones, or other articles of chapter 68;
   (b) Machinery or appliances (e.g., pumps) of ceramic material and ceramic parts of machinery or appliances of any material (chapter 69);
   (c) Laboratory glassware (heading 7017); machinery, appliances, or other articles for technical uses or parts thereof, of glass (heading 7019 or 7020);
   (d) Articles of heading 7321 or 7322 or similar articles of other base metals (chapters 74-76 or 78-81);
   (e) Vacuum cleaners (heading 8508);
   (f) Electromechanical domestic appliances (heading 8509); digital cameras (heading 8525);
   (g) Radiators for section XVII articles;
   (h) Hand-operated mechanical floor sweepers, not motorized (heading 9603).

2. Subject to section XVI note 3 and chapter 84 note 11: machine or appliance matching description in headings 8401-8424 OR heading 8486, AND also matching headings 8425-8480 → classify under the former group or heading 8486, NOT the latter group.

   (A) Heading 8419 does NOT cover:
       (i) Germination plant, incubators, or brooders (heading 8436);
       (ii) Grain dampening machines (heading 8437);
       (iii) Diffusing apparatus for sugar juice extraction (heading 8438);
       (iv) Machinery for heat-treatment of textile yarns, fabrics, or made up textile articles (heading 8451);
